         <NarrativeTitle>Original Narrative</NarrativeTitle>
         <NarrativeText> On Friday, September 22,2023, at approximately 1053 hours the Maryland State Police Cumberland Barrack was contacted by John Hare in reference to an incident that occurred on September 20,2023, between staff members at Green Ridge Youth Center (10700 Fifteen Mile Creek Road South East Flintstone, MD 21530). It was summarized that two of the staff members had verbal remarks with one another during their shift and possibly physical contact. This led to an altercation outside the facility after their work shifts. During that altercation one of the individuals was alleged to be in possession of a firearm. It should be noted that staff of the facility park their vehicles on Fifteen Mile Creek Road and walk to the facility down a flight of stairs. Due to the location where staff are required to park their vehicles, the firearm was not on the state facility property. There are no surveillance cameras in the area where the off premise incident occurred. None of the witnesses captured the events with personal video recording devices (i.e.: cell phone camera footage).   Hare advised that he had collected written statements from several employees that witnessed the incident as well as the two primary employees involved. Several additional witnesses were remaining to complete written statements. An internal investigation is being conducted by the facility. It was determined Group Life Manager Donovan Vinson and RA Thomas Pittman were the involved parties. It is claimed that Pittman waited outside at his vehicle, grabbed something (allegedly a firearm) from the trunk, and stood at driver side of his vehicle. Upon Vinson leaving the facility an additional verbal altercation occurred. It was claimed that then Pittman chambered a round into the firearm. This was described as being heard audibly and not seen. There was no allegation that Pittman pointed a firearm in the direction of anyone.    On September 22, 2023, at approximately 1300 hours I consulted with Deputy States Attorney Linda Thomas, in person, with the limited details associated to this incident. It was determined the additional witness statements were needed to make a conclusion and continue the investigation. The involved state employees, Donovan Vinson and Thomas Pittman, are administratively suspended pending the investigation.    This case remains OPEN for further investigation.  All the above events occurred in Allegany County, Maryland. </NarrativeText>
