         <NarrativeText>  At this time further in person interviews are pending scheduling if applicable. As noted in the initial narrative, a concurrent internal investigation is being conducted under the authority of the administrative structure that oversees the juvenile detention state facility. At the time of the incident being reported, other witnesses, which may be critical to the event, had not been interviewed or had provided written statements to the administration. The incident was not reported at the time of occurrence. In addition to not having the supplementary information, all the witnesses were not present at the facility due to it not being their work hours. If completed, the information has not been received by the Maryland State Police. The statements are required to thoroughly conduct interviews and determine who may have involvement.    This case remains OPEN.    All the above events occurred in Allegany County, Maryland.</NarrativeText>
