         <NarrativeTitle>Supplement #2 Narrative</NarrativeTitle>
         <NarrativeText>  On Friday, December 15, 2023, at approximately 1930 hours, I, Senior Trooper E. Wilson #6100, interviewed Rashaan Jordan Haines (DOB: 2/3/2000). Haines claimed that he saw Pittman display a handgun on the night of the incident, but could not describe the firearm. It should be noted that Haines is a suspect in a non-related incident that occurred two days after this incident. Due to conflicting information for this case, as well as the other, Haines is not believed to be a credible source for statements.      On the same date at approximately 1930 hours, I conducted an in person interview of the suspect of this incident, Thomas Pittman. Pittman was advised his Advise of Miranda Rights utilizing a MSP Form 180. Pittman signed the document and stated that he was willing to speak about the incident without counsel. Pittman described his recollection of the events that occurred during the incident. Pittman made no statements that were inconsistent with the written document he provided Green Ridge Youth Center. Pittman stated that at no time did he produce or brandish a firearm and did not deny any of the verbal altercations that occurred. Pittman admitted that he should not have reacted the way that transpired to a supervisor, but added it should have been handled differently by Vinson.     I carefully reviewed each of the written statements that were provided of the staff members that worked during the incident. Of the fifteen individuals information supplied to me as witnesses or involved, ten were received. Due to no video footage to provide unbiased view of the incident, I contacted the Allegany County District Court States Attorney Office for additional consultation. Upon presentation of the known facts, it was recommended by Senior States Attorney Kelty, there is no sufficient evidence to complete an application of charges from the states position. I contacted the victim Donavin Vinson to advise the status of the case and inform him that he may pursue charges from his perspective. Vinson stated that he will not be completing a charging document at this time and is currently awaiting his administrative investigation results.    It should be noted Pittman has been terminated from the facility due to being on probation at the time of the incident. He is awaiting the final disposition documents for termination. Vinson has been demoted and moved to Backbone Mountain Youth Center.    As noted above the victim is aware of the case status.    Case CLOSED. UNFOUNDED.   All the above events occurred in Allegany County, Maryland.</NarrativeText>
